I"`	<h3 id="led">LED</h3>

<p>The default RGB LED on-board which is <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">GPIO48</code>, does not seem to work with ESPHome. So, wireup a simple LED and resistor to <a href="https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/latest/esp32s3/hw-reference/esp32s3/user-guide-devkitc-1.html#pin-layout"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">GPIO5</code> pin on the board</a>.</p>

<h3 id="compile-and-upload">Compile and upload</h3>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://esphome.io/guides/cli.html#compile-command">Compile</a> firmware for this board</p>

    <div class="language-sh highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> esphome compile blinky-esphome-esp32s3.yaml
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Plug into the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">USB</code> port of the board and check the port address</p>

    <div class="language-sh highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> <span class="nv">$ </span><span class="nb">ls</span> /dev/cu.<span class="k">*</span>

 /dev/cu.Bluetooth-Incoming-Port  /dev/cu.usbmodem14101
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://esphome.io/guides/cli.html#upload-command">Upload</a> the firmware</p>

    <div class="language-sh highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> esphome upload <span class="nt">--device</span> /dev/cu.usbmodem14101 blinky-esphome-esp32s3.yaml
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 id="access-logs">Access logs</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Unplug and plug into the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">UART</code> port of the board</li>
  <li>
    <p>Check the new port address</p>

    <div class="language-sh highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> <span class="nv">$ </span><span class="nb">ls</span> /dev/cu.<span class="k">*</span>
 /dev/cu.Bluetooth-Incoming-Port  /dev/cu.SLAB_USBtoUART  /dev/cu.usbserial-1410
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Access the <a href="https://esphome.io/guides/cli.html#logs-command">logs</a></p>

    <div class="language-sh highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> esphome logs <span class="nt">--device</span> /dev/cu.usbserial-1410 blinky-esphome-esp32s3.yaml
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ol>
:ET